INSERT INTO `t_sheet` VALUES (82, NULL, 'J', 'O\'Byrne, M$$Pakrashi, V$$Schoefs, F$$Ghosh, B', 'O\'Byrne, Michael$$Pakrashi, Vikram$$Schoefs, Franck$$Ghosh, Bidisha', 'A Stereo-Matching Technique for Recovering 3D Information from$$Underwater Inspection Imagery', 'COMPUTER-AIDED CIVIL AND INFRASTRUCTURE ENGINEERING', 'English', 'Article', 'Underwater inspections stand to gain from using stereo imaging systems to collect three-dimensional measurements. Although many stereo-matching algorithms have been devised to solve the correspondence problem, that is, find the same points in multiple images, these algorithms often perform poorly when applied to images of underwater scenes due to the poor visibility and the complex underwater light field. This article presents a new stereo-matching algorithm, called PaLPaBEL (Pyramidal Loopy Propagated BELief) that is designed to operate on challenging imagery. At its core, PaLPaBEL is a semiglobal method based on a loopy belief propagation message passing algorithm applied on a Markov random field. A pyramidal scheme is adopted that enables wide disparity ranges and high-resolution images to be handled efficiently. For performance evaluation, PaLPaBEL is applied to underwater stereo images captured under various visibility conditions in a laboratory setting, and to synthetic imagery created in a virtual underwater environment. The technique is also demonstrated on stereo images obtained from a real-world inspection. The successful results indicate that PaLPaBEL is well suited for underwater application and has value as a tool for the cost-effective inspection of marine structures.', '[O\'Byrne, Michael; Pakrashi, Vikram] Univ Coll Dublin, Sch Mech & Mat Engn, Dynam Syst & Risk Lab, Dublin, Ireland.$$[O\'Byrne, Michael; Pakrashi, Vikram] Univ Coll Dublin, Marine Renewable Energy Ireland MaREI, Dublin, Ireland.$$[Schoefs, Franck] Univ Nantes, Univ Bretagne Loire, Res Inst Civil Engn & Mech GeM Sea, Nantes, France.$$[Schoefs, Franck] CNRS, UMR 6183, FR 3473, Littoral Res Inst IUML, Nantes, France.$$[Schoefs, Franck] CAPACITES Soc, IXEAD, Nantes, France.$$[Ghosh, Bidisha] Trinity Coll Dublin, Dept Civil Struct & Environm Engn, Dublin, Ireland.', 'University College Dublin; University College Dublin; Nantes Universite;$$Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique (CNRS); CNRS - Institute$$for Engineering & Systems Sciences (INSIS); Trinity College Dublin', 'Pakrashi, V (corresponding author), Univ Coll Dublin, Sch Mech & Mat Engn, Dynam Syst & Risk Lab, Dublin, Ireland.; Pakrashi, V (corresponding author), Univ Coll Dublin, Marine Renewable Energy Ireland MaREI, Dublin, Ireland.', 'vikram.pakrashi@ucd.ie', 'Pakrashi, Vikram/0000-0002-8318-3521; Ghosh, Bidisha/0000-0002-1924-3040', 'Alagoz BB, 2008, ONCUBILIM ALGORITHM, V8, P1$$[Anonymous], OPTICAL ENG$$[Anonymous], P IEEE INT C IM PROC$$Bianco G, 2013, SENSORS-BASEL, V13, P11007, DOI 10.3390/s130811007$$Birchfield S, 1998, IEEE T PATTERN ANAL, V20, P401, DOI 10.1109/34.677269$$Bruno F, 2011, ISPRS J PHOTOGRAMM, V66, P508, DOI 10.1016/j.isprsjprs.2011.02.009$$BUSBY RF, 1979, OCEAN ENG, V6, P355$$Byrne J, 2017, J IMAGING, V3, DOI 10.3390/jimaging3020015$$CANNY J, 1986, IEEE T PATTERN ANAL, V8, P679, DOI 10.1109/TPAMI.1986.4767851$$Coughlan J. M., 2010, ASSESSMENT GENUS EUA, P1$$Cyganek B., 2009, INTRO 3D COMPUTER VI$$Estes AC, 2003, J BRIDGE ENG, V8, P374, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)1084-0702(2003)8:6(374)$$Furukawa Y, 2010, IEEE T PATTERN ANAL, V32, P1362, DOI 10.1109/TPAMI.2009.161$$GALLWEY TJ, 1986, HUM FACTORS, V28, P595, DOI 10.1177/001872088602800509$$Gaurier B., 2014, 14 JOURN HYDR VAL DE$$Giachetti A, 2000, IMAGE VISION COMPUT, V18, P247, DOI 10.1016/S0262-8856(99)00018-9$$Hartley R., 2003, MULTIPLE VIEW GEOMET$$Hartley RI, 1999, INT J COMPUT VISION, V35, P115, DOI 10.1023/A:1008115206617$$Hartley RI, 1997, IEEE T PATTERN ANAL, V19, P580, DOI 10.1109/34.601246$$Ho Y.-S., 2013, ERA INTERACTIVE MEDI, P363$$KANADE T, 1994, IEEE T PATTERN ANAL, V16, P