INSERT INTO `t_sheet` VALUES (91, NULL, 'J', 'Zeng, ZQ$$Xu, JP$$Wu, SY$$Shen, MB', 'Zeng, Ziqiang$$Xu, Jiuping$$Wu, Shiyong$$Shen, Manbin', 'Antithetic Method-Based Particle Swarm Optimization for a Queuing$$Network Problem with Fuzzy Data in Concrete Transportation Systems', 'COMPUTER-AIDED CIVIL AND INFRASTRUCTURE ENGINEERING', 'English', 'Article', 'The aim of this article is to develop an antithetic method-based particle swarm optimization to solve a queuing network problem with fuzzy data for concrete transportation systems. The concrete transportation system at the Jinping-I Hydropower Project is considered the prototype and is extended to a generalized queuing network problem. The decision maker needs to allocate a limited number of vehicles and unloading equipment in multiple stages to the different queuing network transportation paths to improve construction efficiency by minimizing both the total operational costs and the construction duration. A multiple objective decision-making model is established which takes into account the constraints and the fuzzy data. To deal with the fuzzy variables in the model, a fuzzy expected value operator, which uses an optimistic-pessimistic index, is introduced to reflect the decision maker\'s attitude. The particular nature of this model requires the development of an antithetic method-based particle swarm optimization algorithm. Instead of using a traditional updating method, an antithetic particle-updating mechanism is designed to automatically control the particle-updating in the feasible solution space. Results and a sensitivity analysis for the Jinping-I Hydropower Project are presented to demonstrate the performance of our optimization method, which was proved to be very effective and efficient compared to the actual data from the project and other metaheuristic algorithms.', '[Zeng, Ziqiang; Xu, Jiuping] Sichuan Univ, Uncertainty Decis Making Lab, Chengdu 610064, Peoples R China.$$[Xu, Jiuping] Sichuan Univ, State Key Lab Hydraul & Mt River Engn, Chengdu 610065, Peoples R China.$$[Wu, Shiyong; Shen, Manbin] Ertan Hydropower Dev Co Ltd, Chengdu, Peoples R China.', 'Sichuan University; Sichuan University', 'Xu, JP (corresponding author), Sichuan Univ, State Key Lab Hydraul & Mt River Engn, Chengdu 610065, Peoples R China.', 'xujiuping@scu.edu.cn', 'Zeng, Ziqiang/0000-0003-1782-2804; ', 'Abramov VM, 2001, QUEUEING SYST, V38, P149, DOI 10.1023/A:1010954214228$$Adeli H, 1997, J CONSTR ENG M ASCE, V123, P450, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-9364(1997)123:4(450)$$Adeli H, 2000, J TRANSP ENG, V126, P464, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-947X(2000)126:6(464)$$Adeli H, 2003, J TRANSP ENG, V129, P484, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-947X(2003)129:5(484)$$Adeli H, 1998, J CONSTR ENG M, V124, P18, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-9364(1998)124:1(18)$$Adeli H., 1995, MACHINE LEARNING NEU$$Amiri GG, 2012, COMPUT-AIDED CIV INF, V27, P711, DOI 10.1111/j.1467-8667.2012.00783.x$$Anghinolfi D, 2009, EUR J OPER RES, V193, P73, DOI 10.1016/j.ejor.2007.10.044$$Balsamo S, 2003, PERFORM EVALUATION, V51, P269, DOI 10.1016/S0166-5316(02)00099-8$$Bliemer MCJ, 2007, TRANSPORT RES REC, P14, DOI 10.3141/2029-02$$Bolat B, 2013, APPL SOFT COMPUT, V13, P2633, DOI 10.1016/j.asoc.2012.11.023$$Casale G, 2011, PERFORM EVALUATION, V68, P180, DOI 10.1016/j.peva.2010.08.026$$Chen SP, 2007, EUR J OPER RES, V177, P445, DOI 10.1016/j.ejor.2005.09.040$$Choi DI, 2007, EUR J OPER RES, V178, P463, DOI 10.1016/j.ejor.2005.12.036$$Clerc M, 2002, IEEE T EVOLUT COMPUT, V6, P58, DOI 10.1109/4235.985692$$Daduna H, 2002, J APPL PROBAB, V39, P865, DOI 10.1017/S0021900200022105$$De Vuyst S, 2002, PERFORM EVALUATION, V48, P103, DOI 10.1016/S0166-5316(02)00033-0$$DUBOIS D, 1978, INT J SYST SCI, V9, P613, DOI 10.1080/00207727808941724$$Dubois D., 1998, POSSIBILITY THEORY A$$Dubois D, 2012, FUZZY SET SYST, V192, P3, DOI 10.1016/j.fss.2010.11.007$$Eberhart RC, 2001, IEEE C EVOL COMPUTAT, P81, DOI 10.1109/CEC.2001.934374$$Fougères AJ, 2013, INTEGR COMPUT-AID E, V20, P259, 