INSERT INTO `t_sheet` VALUES (118, NULL, 'J', 'Zhao, MH$$Liu, Y$$Wang, HN$$Xu, XN$$Xu, SJ', 'Zhao, Mohan$$Liu, Yu$$Wang, Hainian$$Xu, Xinnan$$Xu, Shaojie', 'Modeling and validation of impact forces for back-calculation of$$pavement surface moduli', 'COMPUTER-AIDED CIVIL AND INFRASTRUCTURE ENGINEERING', 'English', 'Article; Early Access', 'When an impact load is sufficiently small, its influence on the pavement structure is mainly from the surface layer material. To explore the influence depth of an impact load and back-calculation of the pavement surface modulus, both numerical calculation and experimental testing were conducted, and the results are presented in this paper. The numerical calculation was performed through a DEM-FDM-coupled model. After a new modulus back-calculation algorithm is formed by analyzing the numerical modeling results, experimental tests were also conducted for verification, and the results were analyzed. The max value of the falling weight impact force was closely related to the elastic modulus of the material, and the influence depth was controllable. Finally, it is proved that the method can be used to calculate the surface layer modulus and estimate the surface layer thickness.', '[Zhao, Mohan; Liu, Yu; Wang, Hainian; Xu, Xinnan; Xu, Shaojie] Changan Univ, Key Lab Special Area Highway Engn, Minist Educ, Xian, Peoples R China.$$[Liu, Yu] Changan Univ, Key Lab Special Area Highway Engn, Minist Educ, Xian 710064, Peoples R China.', 'Chang\'an University; Chang\'an University', 'Liu, Y (corresponding author), Changan Univ, Key Lab Special Area Highway Engn, Minist Educ, Xian 710064, Peoples R China.', 'yul@chd.edu.cn', NULL, 'Bajwa R, 2020, COMPUT-AIDED CIV INF, V35, P1009, DOI 10.1111/mice.12544$$Fwa TF, 1997, TRANSPORT RES REC, P134, DOI 10.3141/1570-16$$Goktepe AB, 2006, ADV ENG SOFTW, V37, P421, DOI 10.1016/j.advengsoft.2005.10.001$$Gopalakrishnan K, 2010, P I CIVIL ENG-TRANSP, V163, P211, DOI 10.1680/tran.2010.163.4.211$$Hamim A, 2018