INSERT INTO `t_sheet` VALUES (128, NULL, 'J', 'Kim, DJ$$Liu, HB$$Xu, XD$$Lu, HY$$Wayson, R$$Rodgers, MO$$Guensler, R', 'Kim, Daejin$$Liu, Haobing$$Xu, Xiaodan$$Lu, Hongyu$$Wayson, Roger$$Rodgers, Michael O.$$Guensler, Randall', 'Distributed computing for region-wide line source dispersion modeling', 'COMPUTER-AIDED CIVIL AND INFRASTRUCTURE ENGINEERING', 'English', 'Article', 'This work introduces a parallelly distributed computing technique to quantify the traffic-related pollutant concentrations at regional scales. The U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA)-recommended dispersion model AERMOD involves complex model setup that requires extensive data inputs with strict formatting rules. These strict requirements increase the likelihood of human errors, especially in larger-scale high-resolution dispersion modeling. The paper presents a streamlined framework that integrates the processes of data preparation, link and receptor configuration, and mobile source emissions modeling. The emissions model is then connected with dispersion model through a parallel computing system. Such linkages allow high-resolution traffic-related air quality impacts to be estimated at the regional scales with high computational efficiency. The tool can be used by a broad audience, including any stakeholders interested in mobile source emissions modeling, and near-road pollutant concentration modeling under the National Environmental Policy Act, and Clean Air Act transportation and air quality conformity analysis.', '[Kim, Daejin] Gangneung Wonju Natl Univ, Gangneung Si, Gangwon Do, South Korea.$$[Liu, Haobing] Univ New Mexico, Dept Civil Construct & Environm Engn, Albuquerque, NM 87131 USA.$$[Xu, Xiaodan; Lu, Hongyu; Rodgers, Michael O.; Guensler, Randall] Georgia Inst Technol, Dept Civil & Environm Engn, Atlanta, GA USA.$$[Wayson, Roger] AECOM, Cottonwood Shores, TX USA.', 'Kangnung Wonju National University; University of New Mexico; University$$System of Georgia; Georgia Institute o