INSERT INTO `t_sheet` VALUES (170, NULL, 'J', 'Sundin, S$$Braban-Ledoux, C', 'Sundin, S$$Braban-Ledoux, C', 'Artificial intelligence-based decision support technologies in pavement$$management', 'COMPUTER-AIDED CIVIL AND INFRASTRUCTURE ENGINEERING', 'English', 'Review', 'The field of road pavement engineering has seen an explosion of artificial intelligence-based applications since the late 1980s. Such applications are found at key stages of the decision process involved in pavement management. In the analysis phase, they perform pavement diagnosis and deterioration modeling tasks. In the design phase, they enable rehabilitation needs to be assessed and contribute to the identification and selection of maintenance actions. Finally, in the choice phase, they are applied for priority programming of rehabilitation and maintenance. They either represent alternative approaches to existing systems or collaborate to make the overall system more efficient. The purpose of this article is to summarize the findings of up-to-dare research articles concerning the application of artificial intelligence to pavement management and to illustrate the potential such tools can offer to pavement engineers. Artificial intelligence techniques include expert systems, artificial neural networks, fuzzy logic genetic algorithms, and hybrid systems.', 'Dalarna Univ, Sch Transportat & Soc, S-78188 Borlange, Sweden.', 'Dalarna University', 'Sundin, S (corresponding author), Dalarna Univ, Sch Transportat & Soc, S-78188 Borlange, Sweden.', 'ssn@du.se', NULL, 'Alsugair AM, 1998, J COMPUT CIVIL ENG, V12, P249, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)0887-3801(1998)12:4(249)$$[Anonymous], 1998, DECIS SUPPORT SYST$$[Anonymous], 1997, LOCAL AGENCY PAVEMEN$$[Anonymous], TRANSPORTATION RES R$$Attohokine N.O., 1994, 3 INT C MAN PAV SAN$$Banan MR, 1996, J TRANSP ENG-ASCE, V122, P358, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-947X(1996)122:5(358)$$BELKASIM SO, 1991, PATTERN RECOGN, V24, P1117, DOI 10.1016/0031-3203(91)90140-Z$$CHOU CJ, 1996, TRANS