INSERT INTO `t_sheet` VALUES (247, NULL, 'J', 'Sushma, MB$$Maji, A', 'Sushma, M. B.$$Maji, Avijit', 'A modified motion planning algorithm for horizontal highway alignment$$development', 'COMPUTER-AIDED CIVIL AND INFRASTRUCTURE ENGINEERING', 'English', 'Article', 'A horizontal alignment can be represented by three key factors: number of horizontal points of intersection (HPIs), their locations, and corresponding horizontal curve radii. Deciding all the three factors simultaneously requires extensive effort, which is not practically feasible in the manual alignment development process. Most available computer-aided methods prioritize some or all the three factors in the automated alignment development processes. However, approximation in HPI location or pre-selection of HPI number and curve radius are the few limitations of these methods. This study presents a modified motion-planning based algorithm for developing new horizontal alignments with optimized costs and impacts. It simultaneously uses a low-discrepancy sampling technique to develop increasingly dense potential HPIs, rapidly exploring random trees to find a suitable number of intermediate HPIs at appropriate locations and sequential quadratic algorithm to select optimally fitted curve radii. The proposed algorithm is integrated with the GIS database for realistic location-dependent cost and environmental impact assessment. Two real-world study areas were selected to compare the results with the one reported in the literature and to evaluate backtracking capability. Results indicated the proficiency of the proposed algorithm in developing new alignments. The sensitivity analyses revealed the effect of design speed and right-of-way width on the alignment generation. The proposed algorithm can automate the new horizontal highway alignment development process and support highway engineers in planning and development.', '[Sushma, M. B.; Maji, Avijit] Indian Inst Technol, Dept Civil Engn, Mumbai 400076, Maharashtra, India.', 'Indian Institute of Technology System (IIT System); Indian Institute of$$Technology (IIT) - Bombay', 'Maji, A (corresponding author), Indian Inst Technol, Dept Civil Engn, Mumbai 400076, Maharashtra, India.', 'avimaji@iitb.ac.in', 'Maji, Avijit/0000-0001-6460-4805; MB, Sushma/0000-0002-8353-1805', '[Anonymous], 2011, POL GEOM DES HIGHW S$$Audet C, 2006, SIAM J OPTIMIZ, V17, P188, DOI 10.1137/040603371$$BHUVAN, 2018, INDIAN GEOPLATFORM I$$Bosurgi G, 2012, COMPUT-AIDED CIV INF, V27, DOI 10.1111/j.1467-8667.2011.00750.x$$Bosurgi G, 2016, J COMPUT CIVIL ENG, V30, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)CP.1943-5487.0000452$$Casal G, 2017, TRANSPORT RES C-EMER, V74, P261, DOI 10.1016/j.trc.2016.11.019$$Cheng JF, 2006, J TRANSP ENG, V132, P913, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-947X(2006)132:12(913)$$Easa SM, 2008, COMPUT-AIDED CIV INF, V23, P560, DOI 10.1111/j.1467-8667.2008.00560.x$$Goktepe A. Burak, 2009, Turkish Journal of Engineering and Environmental Sciences, V33, P105, DOI 10.3906/muh-0904-1$$Hare WL, 2011, EUR J OPER RES, V215, P470, DOI 10.1016/j.ejor.2011.06.011$$Hassan Y, 1997, J TRANSP ENG-ASCE, V123, P60, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-947X(1997)123:1(60)$$de Frutos SH, 2017, COMPUT-AIDED CIV INF, V32, P952, DOI 10.1111/mice.12302$$Jha, 2017, ADV TRANSPORTATION S, V41, P51$$Jha MK, 2004, TRANSPORT RES A-POL, V38, P455, DOI 10.1016/j.tra.2004.04.001$$Jha MK, 2000, TRANSPORT RES REC, P241$$JHA MK, 2006, ADV TRANSPORT, V19$$Jong J. C., 1998, THESIS$$Jong JC, 2000, COMPUT-AIDED CIV INF, V15, P261, DOI 10.1111/0885-9507.00190$$Jong JC, 2003, TRANSPORT RES B-METH, V37, P107, DOI 10.1016/S0191-2615(01)00047-9$$Kang MW, 2013, TRANSPORT RES C-EMER, V31, P99, DOI 10.1016/j.trc.2013.03.002$$Kang MW, 2012, TRANSPORT RES C-EMER, V21, P257, DOI 10.1016/j.trc.2011.09.006$$KARRI GAK, 2012, TRANSP RES BOARD TRB$$Kolda TG, 2005, SIAM J OPTIMIZ, V16, P563, DOI 10.1137/040603589$$LaValle S. M., 2006, PLANNING ALGORITHMS, DOI [10.1017/CBO9780511546877., DOI 10.1017/CBO9780511546877]$$LaValle SM, 2001, ALG