INSERT INTO `t_sheet` VALUES (341, NULL, 'J', 'Song, WK$$Kim, SE$$Ma, SS', 'Song, Weon-Keun$$Kim, Seung-Eock$$Ma, Sang Soo', 'Nonlinear analysis of steel cable-stayed bridges', 'COMPUTER-AIDED CIVIL AND INFRASTRUCTURE ENGINEERING', 'English', 'Article', 'In this study, a nonlinear inelastic analysis model using a softening plastic-hinge approach is proposed for predicting the ultimate load-carrying capacity of steel cable-stayed bridges. The ultimate load-carrying capacity analysis is done starting from the initial shape determination due to bridge dead load. The proposed model can consider both geometric and material nonlinearities in the nonlinear inelastic analysis for the example bridges. The load-displacement curves of the example bridges predicted by both the proposed model and the commercial code ABAQUS are compared with each other to verify the accuracy of solutions. Identical solutions between them are found. A parametric study on the example bridges is presented and their ultimate behavior is discussed.', 'Korea Infrastruct Safety & Technol Corp, Anyang, South Korea.$$Sejong Univ, Construct Technol Res Inst, Seoul, South Korea.', 'Sejong University', 'Song, WK (corresponding author), Korea Infrastruct Safety & Technol Corp, Anyang, South Korea.', 'bauman98@hanmail.net', NULL, 'ADELI H, 1995, COMPUT STRUCT, V54, P267, DOI 10.1016/0045-7949(94)00332-W$$*AISC, 2001, LOAD RES FACT DES SP$$[Anonymous], 1998, AASHTO LRFD BRIDG DE$$Boonyapinyo V, 1994, J STRUCT ENG, V40A, P295$$CHEN WF, 1992, STABILITY DESIGN STE, P380$$ELZANATY MH, 1983, J STRUCT ENG-ASCE, V109, P353, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-9445(1983)109:2(353)$$Ernst J.H., 1965, BANINGENIEUR, V40, P52$$FLEMING JF, 1979, COMPUT STRUCT, V10, P621, DOI 10.1016/0045-7949(79)90006-3$$Gimsing NJ., 1983, CABLE SUPPORTED BRID$$Hibbitt Karlsson Sorensen, 2001, ABAQUS STAND US MAN$$KANOKNUKULCHAI W, 1993, J CONSTR STEEL RES, V26, P249, DOI 10.1016/0143-974X(93)90039-U$$Kim SE, 1996, J STRUCT ENG-ASCE, V122, P1259, DOI 10