INSERT INTO `t_sheet` VALUES (346, NULL, 'J', 'Reddy, HR$$Varghese, K', 'Reddy, HR$$Varghese, K', 'Automated path planning for mobile crane lifts', 'COMPUTER-AIDED CIVIL AND INFRASTRUCTURE ENGINEERING', 'English', 'Article', 'Planning the lift path of a crane is an important subtask within the heavy-lift planning process. This paper reports the work done toward applying configuration space (C-space) and search concepts to develop a tool to identify lift paths that satisfies the planning requirements. The C-space is generated using an interference detection technique. Two levels of heuristic search are performed within the C-space. The first search is a heuristic depth search to determine the obstacle-free lift paths. The second search performs a more detailed optimization of the path within a constrained search space. The tool can be used within the AutoCad environment and is based on program modules developed using AutoLisp and external programs. The system was tested on a number of problems. It was found that the system was capable of generating good paths in complex situations.', 'Indian Inst Technol, Dept Civil Engn, Madras 60036, Tamil Nadu, India.', 'Indian Institute of Technology System (IIT System); Indian Institute of$$Technology (IIT) - Madras', 'Varghese, K (corresponding author), Indian Inst Technol, Dept Civil Engn, Madras 60036, Tamil Nadu, India.', NULL, NULL, 'ALEXANDER S, 1992, MICROSTATION MANAGER, V2, P1$$BENNET C, 1994, P ASCE SPEC C ROB CH$$*BROWN ROOT INC, 1991, C A R COMP AID RIGG$$*COMP CRAN, 2000, CRAN SEL PLANN SOFTW$$HORNADAY WC, 1993, J CONSTR ENG M ASCE, V119, P498, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-9364(1993)119:3(498)$$JOHNSON J, 1995, MECHATRONICS DESIGNI, V2$$Kunigahalli R., 1998, Computer-Aided Civil and Infrastructure Engineering, V13, P275, DOI 10.1111/0885-9507.00106$$Latombe J.-C., 2012, ROBOT MOTION PLANNIN, V124$$Lin KL, 1996, J CONSTR ENG M ASCE, V122, P354, DOI 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-9364(1996)122:4(354)$$LOZANOPEREZ T, 1983, IEEE T COMPUT