INSERT INTO `t_sheet` VALUES (474, NULL, 'J', 'Akinyemi, EO$$Zuidgeest, MHP', 'Akinyemi, EO$$Zuidgeest, MHP', 'Managing transportation infrastructure for sustainable development', 'COMPUTER-AIDED CIVIL AND INFRASTRUCTURE ENGINEERING', 'English', 'Article', 'Major requirements for operationalization of the concept of sustainable development in urban transportation infrastructure operations management are presented. In addition, it is shown that the current approach to management is incompatible with the requirements for sustainable urban development. Consequently, the conceptual framework of a desirable approach is proposed. The philosophy of this approach is that the basic mission of infrastructure operations management is to obtain and maintain the maximum levels of people and goods mobility possible within the resources and environmental capacities in an area. A mathematical model is presented for obtaining the desirable levels and characteristics of traffic on each segment of an urban transportation network. In addition, three illustrative applications of the implemented model are presented.', 'Int Inst Infrastruct Hydraul & Environm Engn, IHE Delft, Dept Municipal Infrastruct, NL-2601 DA Delft, Netherlands.$$Univ Twente, Dept Civil Engn, NL-7500 AE Enschede, Netherlands.', 'IHE Delft Institute for Water Education; University of Twente', 'Akinyemi, EO (corresponding author), Int Inst Infrastruct Hydraul & Environm Engn, IHE Delft, Dept Municipal Infrastruct, NL-2601 DA Delft, Netherlands.', 'aki@ihe.nl', NULL, 'ABBOTT PG, 1995, ENV ASSESSMENT TRAFF$$AKINYEMI E, 2000, WORLD TRANSPORT POLI, V6, P31$$AKINYEMI EO, 1997, 1997 ITE INT C TAMP, P191$$AKINYEMI EO, 1995, P 23 EUR TRANSP FOR, P23$$AKINYEMI EO, 1999, TRE024 IHE$$AKINYEMI EO, 1998, TRE022 IHE$$ALMASRI EH, 2000, THESIS IHE DELFT DEL$$[Anonymous], 1964, TRAFF ASS MAN$$[Anonymous], 1997, CRITICAL MASS TRANSP$$Donaghy KP, 1998, TRANSPORT RES D-TR E, V3, P59, DOI 10.1016/S1361-9209(97)00016-3$$JORDAN DR, 1997, TRA